(225, 1, '2019-02-21 10:59:04', '2019-02-21 10:59:04', '<img class=\"size-full wp-image-162 aligncenter\" src=\"http://vietnamexpo.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/VNExpo201704177242123PM_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"480\" height=\"335\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">Visitors at Vietnam Expo 2017. - VNS Photo</span></p>\r\n<em><span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">The 28th Vietnam International Trade Fair (Viet Nam Expo 2018), will be held at ICE Hanoi International Exhibition Fair Center for 4 days from 11 ~ 14 April 2018</span></em><span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\"> .</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">2017 is a prosperous year for bilateral economic cooperation relations between Vietnam and Russia and emphasizes the potential for strong development in the future. At the same time, the two sides agreed to promote the implementation of the Free Trade Agreement (FTA) between Vietnam and the Eurasian Economic Union through the goal of bilateral trade growth between the two countries reaching 20 billion VND. USD in 2020.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">Russia - one of Vietnam \'s strategic economic partners in Europe has confirmed its participation in VIETNAM EXPO this time as a \"guest of honor\". This is a good signal as well as a great opportunity for domestic businesses when participating in the event.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">At the exhibition with an area of ​​nearly 520m2, Russian enterprises will display many products of some key export-import industries such as mechanical production, precision engineering, automation equipment in parallel with many types. product images of industrial biotechnology applications and high-tech electronics.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">Event organizer, Vinexad company said, the upcoming International Trade Fair has an important meaning to enhance optimal and effective trade promotion activities for both sides.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">Besides exhibitors from Russia, the exhibition also attracts many businesses and corporations from other countries and regions such as Korea, Nepal, Thailand, Japan, Singapore and Cuba. Laos, Cambodia, Taiwan and Hong Kong plan to display a variety of high quality and diverse products such as machinery, equipment, construction materials, electronics, information technology (IT), materials Rough and auxiliary, consumer goods (food, agricultural products) as well as household appliances and health care products / services.</span>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em><strong><span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">Bizhub (Vietnam News)</span></strong></em></p>', 'Russian enterprises participate in displaying products in VIETNAM EXPO 2018', '2017 is a prosperous year for bilateral economic cooperation relations between Vietnam and Russia and emphasizes the potential for strong development in the future. At the same time, the two sides agreed to promote the implementation of the Free Trade Agreement (FTA) between Vietnam and the Eurasian Economic Union through the goal of bilateral trade growth between the two countries reaching 20 billion VND. USD in 2020.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'russian-enterprises-participate-in-displaying-products-in-vietnam-expo-2018', '', '', '2019-02-21 10:59:04', '2019-02-21 10:59:04', '', 0, 'http://vietnamexpo.co/?p=225', 0, 'post', '', 0),
