(228, 1, '2019-02-21 11:07:04', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">(NDH) In the morning of April 19, the 27th VietnamExpo international trade fair opened at Hanoi International Exhibition Center with the participation of 500 enterprises from many countries around the world.</span>\n\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">Vietnam Expo international trade fair is organized by Trade Promotion Agency (Ministry of Industry and Trade) and Vinexad Company. This year, with the theme \"Strengthening regional and international economic integration\", the fair attracted 500 enterprises participating with 600 booths. In which, the booths of enterprises come from 16 provinces and cities of Vietnam and 23 countries and territories such as Korea, India, Algeria, Cuba, Cambodia, Thailand, Japan, Mongolia, China, Turkey, Nepal, Korea, Russia ...</span>\n\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">This year the national pavilions are from Korea, Algeria, Cuba, China and Vietnam. In which Korea is currently one of the three major trading partners of Vietnam, by the end of 2016, the total amount of Korean investment registration in Vietnam is up to 57 billion USD. 2017 marked an important milestone, celebrating 25 years of establishing diplomatic relations between Vietnam and Korea. Korean enterprises participated in the biggest fair with 130 enterprises and 138 booths.</span>\n\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">The highlight of this year\'s exhibition is the Export Promotion Forum which took place in the morning of April 20 with the topic of exchanging export market prospects, export policies and impacting this policy on export activities. export, practical experience in trade promotion activities. This is also an opportunity for businesses to participate in fairs to seek partners and promote trade activities.</span>\n\n<img class=\"wp-image-165 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"http://vietnamexpo.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/kira.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"730\" height=\"548\" />\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">Vietnamese enterprises participate in seeking partners at the fair. Photo of Hai Minh</span></em></p>\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">In addition, the Vietnam industrial development and investment promotion booth is organized by the Trade Promotion Department to provide updated information on the investment environment in Vietnam to investors and promotion organizations. Foreign countries, especially investors from Korea and Japan. The organizers said that, through activities at the booth, we will introduce strengths and policies to attract investment of Vietnam to investors, especially in areas such as mining, renewable energy, and weaving. sewing, seafood ...</span>\n\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">Participating in the fair, Mr. Nguyen Hai Ho, Deputy General Director of Hanoi Beer Alcohol Beverage Joint Stock Company (Habeco) said that this fair is one of the best points for Habeco to promote the brand and image. Product photos to domestic and foreign customers, especially international partners</span>\n\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">Deputy General Director of Hapro Nguyen Thi Hai Thanh said that Hapro had direct contracts from the Fair, and the more important thing that Hapro expected was to promote the company\'s image and promote import and export business. at the fair.</span>', '', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2019-02-21 11:07:04', '2019-02-21 11:07:04', '', 0, 'http://vietnamexpo.co/?p=228', 0, 'post', '', 0),
