(252, 1, '2019-03-04 03:14:19', '2019-03-04 03:14:19', '<strong><span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">VIETNAM EXPO - COMPLETE, SHARE, SUCCESS AND SUCCESS!</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">With the history of being one of the most prestigious and long-standing trade promotion events in Vietnam, Vietnam Expo has always affirmed that through every year of organization and in 2019 - after a year of prosperity of the Vietnamese economy. Male, import and export turnover and investment all have achieved good growth signs, we continue to promote the role of an event to promote import and export trade and investment, bringing Vietnamese products to promote. to the world and vice versa.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">Vietnam Expo 2019 will be held from April 10-13, 2019 at ICE International Exhibition Center - 91 Tran Hung Dao, Hoan Kiem, Hanoi. Due to the limited scale of the infrastructure, the Organizing Committee must select the typical enterprises to attend in accordance with the stalls: International Area - Vietnam National Brand Area - Industrial Products Zone - Zone Consumer Food. Up to this point, the organizers and the participating businesses are actively preparing to bring to Vietnam Expo 2019 the most beautiful booths, the latest products and technologies.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-236 size-large\" src=\"http://vietnamexpo.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/VN-Expo-2017-007-1200x800.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">In addition to the eye-catching International area and attracting visitors by the diversity and sophistication in booth design and product decoration, the participation of National Brand Enterprises (VIETNAM VALUE) - display of products Vietnamese branded products associated with the core values: \"Quality - Innovation - Innovation - Pioneering capacity\", to promote the image of a reputable Vietnam in diverse goods and services with High quality, enhancing the awareness of distributors and consumers in general for Vietnamese-valued products, enhancing the competitiveness of Vietnamese Brands in the domestic and foreign markets. According to the participating enterprises, in addition to the demand for domestic promotion, this is also an opportunity for Vietnamese exporters to meet partners and seek to expand the export market of enterprises.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">Not merely attending a Fair to find new sources, at the Vietnam Expo 2019, you will receive the necessary advice on design, market demand research, development of brand ideas. , product packaging through the Zone of Design and Product Development Support by the Korea Design Promotion Institute (KIDP) - Ministry of Commerce, Industry &amp; Energy of Korea in coordination with Trade Promotion Department Vietnam (VIETRADE) organized.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">With us continuing the tour, you will come across a display area with many models, tables, maps - that is the Vietnam Industry Development and Investment Promotion Booth. According to the report of the Foreign Investment Agency (Ministry of Planning and Investment), in 2018, the total newly registered, increased and contributed capital to buy shares of foreign investors (FDI) reached 35 , USD 46 billion, equaling 98.8% compared to the same period in 2017. Estimated foreign direct investment projects have disbursed USD 19.1 billion, up 9.1% compared to the same period in 2017. About Investment sector, foreign investors have invested in 18 sectors, in which processing and manufacturing industries are the fields attracting the most attention of foreign investors with the total capital reached. 16.58 billion USD, accounting for 46.7% of the total registered investment capital. Real estate business is ranked second with total investment of 6.6 billion USD, accounting for 18.6% of the total registered investment capital. The third is the wholesale and retail sector with the total registered investment capital of 3.67 billion USD, accounting for 10.3% of the total registered investment capital.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">Algeria, India, Cambodia, Canada, CH Armenia, Federal Republic of Russia, Cuba, Taiwan, South Korea, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, Nepal, Japan, China are officially countries and territories that were officially present at Vietnam Expo at this time, it is expected that this year\'s Fair will attract businesses to attend from 20 countries and territories, along with over 15,000 trade visitors to visit and work in the 4th time. Fair day.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-237 size-large\" src=\"http://vietnamexpo.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/VN-Expo-2017-031-1200x800.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">Vietnam Expo 2019 is chaired by the Ministry of Industry and Trade, the Department of Trade Promotion and organized by VINEXAD, will be open from 9 am to 6 pm on April 10-13, at the Exhibition Center 91 Tran Hung Dao, Hoan Kiem, Hanoi. Details of the Fair at: www.vnexpocom.vn</span>', 'Introduce', 'With the history of being one of the most prestigious and long-standing trade promotion events in Vietnam, Vietnam Expo has always affirmed that through every year of organization and in 2019 - after a year of prosperity of the Vietnamese economy. Male, import and export turnover and investment all have achieved good growth signs, we continue to promote the role of an event to promote import and export trade and investment, bringing Vietnamese products to promote. to the world and vice versa.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '240-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-04 03:14:19', '2019-03-04 03:14:19', '', 240, 'http://vietnamexpo.co/240-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
